# Experiment Logging Invariant (always-on)

Every experiment entry in `docs/RESEARCH_LOG.md` that is **shipped** or
**reverted** (or `building`/`blocked`) must include:

1. **A status badge** — `SHIPPED ✅` / `REVERTED ❌` / `BUILDING 🔧` /
   `BLOCKED 🚧` — in the heading.
2. **A one-line TL;DR** with the headline number.
3. **A measurement bar chart** — scaled `█` bars with absolute numbers + a
   `~Nx faster` / `regressed` / `unchanged` annotation. Prose-only numbers
   ("14397ms vs 120ms") do **not** count — the comparison must be visible.

Pure ideas (not yet tried) use the idea-entry format (paper / plug-in /
expected delta / status: `idea`) and don't need a chart.

## Why

The experiment log is the most-consulted doc over time. A reader should get
the outcome from the badge + TL;DR + bar chart alone, without reading prose.
Prose-only entries bury the headline and make the log unscannable.

## Complements, doesn't duplicate

The `documentation` rule covers flow/pipeline changes (need an ASCII diagram
of the new flow). This rule covers **experiment result entries** (need a
measurement bar chart). An experiment that changes the pipeline ships both:
the before/after pipeline diagram (documentation rule) AND the measurement
bar chart (this rule).

See the `experiment-logging` skill for the full card format + bar-chart
conventions.
